Title: KitchenAid Artisan — Since 1919
Author: wavelet-director

INT. WARM KITCHEN - MORNING

Close-up: a brown egg cracks against the rim of a stainless bowl, golden yolk dropping in slow motion into a soft cloud of flour. Hand pulls back. The iconic red stand mixer waits, tilt-head paused mid-rise. Window light pours in from the left.

CUT TO:

INT. WARM KITCHEN - MORNING - MACRO

Macro: the spiral dough hook turns at low speed. Pale dough folds over itself, catching shape on every rotation. Single soft window key. Cream and crimson dominate the frame. Time slows.

CUT TO:

INT. WARM KITCHEN - MORNING

Two flour-dusted hands lift a finished round loaf from a black cast-iron pot. Steam rises. The loaf is set on a wooden board next to the stand mixer, which sits clean and quiet in the back of frame, signature red against pale tile.

CUT TO:

INT. WARM KITCHEN - MORNING - BEAUTY HOLD

Locked-off three-quarter beauty hold on the empty stand mixer. Cream and brick tones. A single dust mote drifts across the soft window light. The kitchen is still.

FADE OUT.
